# Verasanth Game Direction

When adding or changing content (dialogue, locations, items, systems), align with the canonical blueprint: **GAME_DIRECTION.md**.

## Tone

- Dark, atmospheric, grounded. Short dialogue; no lore dumps, no high fantasy, no comedy, no modern slang.
- Sensory detail: cold, stone, fog, echoes. Environmental storytelling over exposition.

## World pillars

- **Oppression** — mountain, fog, cold.
- **Decay** — old stone, old magic, old grudges.
- **Subtlety** — NPCs hint; the world suggests rather than explains.
- **Resilience** — people endure and adapt.
- **Environmental storytelling** — walls, objects, spaces tell stories.

City = hub (Verasanth). Runs = zones (mountain, forest, sewer). Districts modular and expandable.

## Key NPCs

- **Kelvaris** — bartender; polite, observant; rumors, quest hooks.
- **Caelir** — weaponsmith; elegant, precise; weapon upgrades, crafted gear.
- **Veyra** — minimal speech, heavy environmental storytelling; rare items, lore fragments.
- **Seris Vantrel** — general trader; calm, enigmatic; goods, consumables, run supplies.
- **Alchemist/Herbalist** — practical, uncanny; potions, buffs, run modifiers.

They speak briefly and meaningfully; never fully explain themselves.

## Technical

- Modular, data-driven zones (e.g. JSON). Stateful NPCs. Simple, atmospheric UI. Avoid overcomplication.

## Constraint

All new content must align with **GAME_DIRECTION.md**. When in doubt, prefer subtle and old/weathered over flashy or explanatory.
